Free flow mobility_16.name: capacityincrease
Free flow mobility_16.text: Induced demand as a result of capacity increase is managed with the promotion of carfree developments through the planning system. The significant decrease in onstreet parking that comes as a result of high adoption rates of shared mobility is used to increase housing density near employment centres and to improve the public realm experience in dense areas. Rezoning of parking places has been integrated into local plans and sustainable funding models enable the investments required to adapt and transform urban spaces. The way cities are built determines mobility needs and how they can be met. Development, urban design and public spaces, building and planning regulations, parking requirements, and other land use policies incentivise compact, accessible, livable, and sustainable cities.
